    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Semiconductor lasers used in Raman spectroscopy that reverse, or flip, the direction of conduction-band electrons as they spin on an axis in the direction of the magnetic field.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
